details.title: Anjanath
details.info: Anjanath spits fiery blasts from its mouth utilizing a unique organ in its throat. Focusing attacks on its throat will make battling it much easier.

Dragon ⭐

details.info: While it uses hardened mud as armor, Barroth can also fling it off its body as an attack. Use water element weapons or your slinger to gradually knock off its mud.

details.title: Bazelgeuse
details.locations:
Ancient Forest
Coral Highlands
Rotten Vale
Wildspire Waste
Elders Recess
details.info: The scales that Bazelgeuse scatters explode with tremendous force, making them extremely deadly. Focus on its leslash to knock it down, and then knock out its scale-generating organs.

details.title: Behemoth
details.info: If you manage to gain enmity, this gives your teammates a massive opening, just remember to stay alive.

details.title: Deviljho
details.blights:
Dragonblight
Defense Down
Fireblight (lava)
Waterblight (water)
Effluvia (Rotten Vale)
details.locations:
Ancient Forest
Coral Highlands
Rotten Vale
Wildspire Waste
Elders Recess
details.info: When enraged, Deviljho's swollen muscles glow a hellish red. It will start spewing a sweeping dragon element attack, so watch your distance. Deviljho stays on the attack even when wounded, but don't give up; keep fighting and you'll come out on top.

details.title: Diablos
details.info: Diablos can be forcibly brought to the surface by using loud sounds. And its charging attack, while devastatingly powerful, can be baited into colliding with a wildspire, momentarily getting the Diablos stuck.

details.title: Black Diablos
details.info: Diablos are much more aggressive against intruders when in heat, and are known to attack enemies in retreat. Do not let your guard down even if you think you've established a safe distance from these monsters.

details.title: Dodogama
details.info: Dodogama collects explosive minerals in its mouth, but doing so weakens its massive jaw. Causing the minerals to detonate while they're still in Dodogama's mouth will create a great opening for an attack.

details.title: Great Girros
details.info: Taking down lesser Girros will make the rest of the pack scatter, and should be a top priority. Breaking the fanslash of a Great Girros will make its paralyzing agent much weaker.

details.title: Great Jagras
details.info: Even after a giant meal, a Great Jagras can use its expanded stomach to attack unsuspecting hunters. Aim for its belly to force it to vomit out its prey and significantly weaken it.

details.title: Jyuratodus
details.elements:
Fire ⭐(:x:)
Water :x:(⭐⭐⭐)
Thunder ⭐⭐⭐(:x:)
Ice ⭐
Dragon ⭐
() when covered in mud.
details.info: It's nearly impossible to fight a Jyuratodus in its swampy home. Coerce it to land, and then use water element weapons or your slinger to slowly chip away its hardened mud armor.

details.title: Kirin
details.info: The lightning a Kirin cloaks itself with has been confirmed to toughen its skin. The key to hunting a Kirin lies in staggering it, using Elderseal weapons, and protecting yourself from and avoiding its lightning attacks.

details.title: Kulu-Ya-Ku
details.info: Kulu-Ya-Ku can use small boulders to shield itself or smash against its enemies. Force it to drop whatever it's holding by using your slinger. You can also frighten it by luring one of its natural enemies.

details.title: Kulve Taroth
details.elements:
Fire :x:(⭐)
Water ⭐⭐
Thunder :x:(⭐⭐⭐)
Ice ⭐⭐⭐(:x:)
Dragon ⭐⭐(⭐)
() when covered in gold.
details.info: An exhaustive investigation is required in order to break Kulve Taroth's giant gold plated horns. Pursue the monster to learn more about it. Gather tracks and recruit hunters to help you further your investigation.

details.title: Kushala Daora
details.info: When confronted by enemies, Kushala's wind shield continuously grows in intensity, eventually deflecting bow and bowgun attacks. Its wind shield can be weakened by staggering it, particularly with weapons with Elderseal capabilities.

details.title: Lavasioth
details.elements:
Fire :x:(⭐)
Water ⭐⭐⭐(⭐⭐)
Thunder ⭐⭐(:x:)
Ice ⭐⭐(:x:)
Dragon ⭐
() when hardened.
details.info: The hardened magma on Lavasioth's body becomes softer as it swims through the lava. Attack its armor immediately after it surfaces to increase your chances of destroying it before it rehardens.

details.title: Legiana
details.info: The membrane that covers its entire body enables Legiana to move with incredible speed. Damaging this membrane should help with slowing it down. Poison attacks have also been known to be effective.

details.title: Lunastra
details.info: Lunastra's high body temperature and dust saps away health unless you use a Cool Drink. Its dust and blue flame explode when it comes into contact with fire, so use a bomb or Crystalburst.

details.title: Nergigante
details.info: Nergigante can recover from wounds almost instantaneously. Regenerated body parts grow harder over time, so attacking them while they're still fresh is the ideal strategy.

details.title: Odogaron
details.info: Odogaron's nasty claws cause heavy bleeding and should be avoided at all costs. Use meat to lure it into traps, stagger it, or coerce it into bouts of rage to tire it out and make it easier to deal with.

details.title: Paolumu
details.info: Paolumu can't move around as freely when its air sacs are deflated. Aim for its inflated body parts, or purposefully draw out its attacks that use up stored air, to gain the upper hand.

details.title: Pukei-Pukei
details.info: Observational reports state that Pukei-Pukei will bully weaker monsters but cower before bigger, stronger monsters. It's prone to retreating at the first sign of danger, so use that to your advantage.

details.title: Radobaan
details.info: Attack it as it rolls around to throw it off balance and knock it down. Chunks of bone can be mined from its body once it's down. Shattering its bone armor is the key to winning a fight against this beast.

details.title: Rathalos
details.info: Rathalos prefer to stay airborne to unleash their myriad attacks, but a well-placed flash bomb or a shot from your slinger can send them crashing to the earth. Wounding their winslash gives them a moment of vulnerability whenever they try to take flight.

details.title: Azure Rathalos
details.info: Counter its airborne onslaught by observing its flight patterns and finding the right moment to knock it out of the sky. Once grounded, it loses its ability to perform consecutive attacks, making the fight much easier.

details.title: Rathian
details.info: Come prepared with fire-resistant armor, and neuter its poison attacks by severing its tail.

details.title: Pink Rathian
details.info: Pink Rathians develop hard shells on different body parts compared to standard Rathians, particularly on their tails. If you're looking to sever its tail, aim for the relatively soft tip of the tail.

details.title: Teostra
details.info: The dust Teostra scatters will spread over a wide area until it finally explodes. Keep an eye on that, as well as the flames it occasionally shields itself in, and aim to stagger it with weapons possessing Elderseal capabilities.

details.title: Tobi-Kadachi
details.info: Use the target camera to avoid getting ambushed from behind as it moves from tree to tree. The key to defeating this monster is to immobilize it and prevent it from reaching a charged state.

details.title: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku
details.info: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku's organs begin to radiate before it releases its blinding pulse, giving you enough time to escape and flank it. Damaging this organ will dramatically decrease the flash's effective shot.

details.title: Uragaan
details.info: A crushing slam from the Uragaan's jaw can send shockwaves across the ground, detonating any explosive rocks in the area. In addition, when an Uragaan is toppled, its body can be mined for ore.

details.title: Vaal Hazak
details.info: Once you've become tainted, inhaling the vapor of the vale causes your own health to drain. Head for areas where the vapor is thin, and if you do get tainted, use nulberries to remove it. Using the miasma skill nullifies it entirely.

details.title: Xeno'Jiiva
details.info: Perhaps as a result of its inability to fully control its own incalculable power, Xeno'jiiva is prone to go into a rampage when its energy-filled limbs take enough damage. Endure its rampage and you may be rewarded with a good opening for attacks.

details.title: Zorah Magdaros
details.info: Normal attacks can't make a dent in its mountain-like shell. Utilize larger weapons such as cannons and ballistae, or directly attack the "magmacore" heat organs that are exposed in parts of its outer shell.

details.title: Ancient Leshen
details.info: If you get trapped by one of Ancient Leshens attacks, a teammate can use a flashpod to get you out.

details.title: Leshen
details.info: The easier counterpart to the Ancient Leshen, this variant proves much easier.

details.title: Banbaro
details.info: Blows to the Banbaro's leslash are an effective counter to its deadly charge. Firing scatternuts or crystalburst mid-charge can halt the beast.

details.title: Beotodus
details.info: Stripping the snow packed on its body will force the monster out into the open. Firing screamer pods can provide an opening to attack: focus on its leg fins to weaken it.

details.title: Nargacuga
details.info: Nargacuga's speed dulls when exhausted, so luring it into turf wars with other monsters is effective. Take care when setting traps, as it will destroy pitfalls when not enraged.

details.title: Velkhana
details.info: Shattering the ice that encases its body neutralizes its freezing breath. The ice walls it forms can be broken to provide platforms for mounting. Torch pods are useful for this.

details.title: Tigrex
details.locations:
Rotten Vale
Hoarfrost Reach
Wildspire Waste
Ancient Forest
Elders Recess
details.info: Ledges and obstacles won't stop Tigrex's charge, so you'll need to steer clear. After enough repetitions the monster will tire and slow down, opening up to counterattacks.

details.title: Shrieking Legiana
details.info: Sufficient damage can knock it out of the sky, and it is especially vulnerable while dive-bombing, making barrel bombs effective. Like other Legiana, poison also works well.

details.title: Barioth
details.info: Break its tail, or especially its foreleslash to mitigate both its offense and its mobility. The monster's hide is extremely tough, but fire elemental attacks should prove effective.

details.title: Glavenus
details.locations:
Ancient Forest
Wildspire Waste
Elders Recess
details.info: Once red hot, its tail will begin to rust and the monster will sharpen it anew with its fanslash, storing the slag to expel as fiery breath. Strike its throat when it glows red.

details.title: Brachydios
details.info: Its scalp secretes a thick slime capable of tripping hunters who step in it. Water will dilute it however, making water and ice attacks to its head and arms effective.

details.title: Fulgur Anjanath
details.elements:
Fire ⭐⭐
Water ⭐⭐(⭐⭐⭐)
Thunder :x:
Ice ⭐⭐⭐(⭐⭐)
Dragon ⭐
() when charged.
details.info: Once it enters an electrified state, its hide hardens, and its attacks deal elemental damage. Focus blows on its head to dissipate the charge.

details.title: Ebony Odogaron
details.info: When frenzied, it uses dragon elemental attacks, but hunters can hit its head with their own elemental attacks to calm it.

details.title: Acidic Glavenus
details.elements:
Fire ⭐⭐⭐
Water ⭐
Thunder ⭐⭐
Ice ⭐
Dragon ⭐⭐(⭐)
() when crystalized.
details.info: The acid on its tail will lower a hunter's defenses on contact, and spreads with time, increasing the shot of its spray. The ailments it inflicts can be removed with defense buff items

details.title: Ruiner Nergigante
details.info: Like its cousins, it attacks with white and black spikes, but also possesses metallic spikes that do not regrow. Break them to greatly reduce the monster's lethality.

details.title: Viper Tobi-Kadachi
details.info: Its agility is its greatest weapon, but also makes it prone to exhaustion. When tired, it grows drastically less mobile. Focus attacks on its soft parts to exhaust it quickly.

details.title: Coral Pukei-Pukei
details.info: After feeding, the water attacks from both ends are enhanced: focus on those two areas to weaken the creature again.

details.title: Nightshade Paolumu
details.info: It uses tail swipes and other blows to bat its soporific breath into a target's path. Stubbornly airborne, using flash pods can drop it to the ground.

details.title: Namielle
details.info: Emitting water causes its coating to decrease, and it becomes vulnerable when dry. Use brightmoss and other slinger fire to remove any nearby sources of water.

details.title: Yian Garuga
details.info: It moves violently with its entire body, enough to break pitfall traps when enraged. Slow it by breaking body parts or baiting out its stamina-intensive beak attacks.

details.title: Shara Ishvalda
details.ailments:
Poison ⭐⭐
Sleep :x:
Paralysis ⭐
Blast ⭐⭐⭐(⭐⭐)
Stun ⭐
() when released.
details.info: Hunters must begin by stripping its sturdy rock armor: bombs and falling rocks are two proven methods. Skills to counter tremors are a boon against its wingtip attacks.

details.title: Savage Deviljho
details.blights:
Defense Down
Dragonblight
Fireblight (lava)
Iceblight (icy)
Waterblight (water)
details.info: The monster grows in strength as it fights and feeds, so preventing it from eating is paramount. Blows to the head are effective. It will ignore hunters around larger prey.

details.title: Blackveil Vaal Hazak
details.info: Damaging areas densely covered by spores appears to dull their activity as a whole. They also shield the monster from light: break the head to make flash pods work.

details.title: Seething Bazelgeuse
details.info: Focus attacks on the enhanced scales to weaken the monster. Reports indicate that puddle pods, crystalburst, and scatternuts are all effective in this regard.

details.title: Scarred Yian Garuga
details.info: Like the normal species, its head is easily breakable, and it's quick to run out of stamina. It behaves differently when flying short distances though, so be careful.

details.title: Gold Rathian
details.info: The hellfire can be dispelled by dealing a set amount of damage to its head, which is extremely tough until broken. Try to destroy it as quickly as possible.

details.title: Silver Rathalos
details.info: The hellfire can be dispelled by dealing a set amount of damage to its head. It lives in tandem with a Gold Rathian, and their breath becomes deadlier still when combined.

details.title: Brute Tigrex
details.info: As with its standard cousins, it will tire after repeated charges, so attempt to bait them out. Breaking its head is an effective way to weaken the monster's roar.

details.title: Zinogre
details.locations:
Guiding Lands
Ancient Forest
Coral Highlands
details.info: When supercharged, parts of the monster become soft, but shock traps no longer work. You can knock it out of supercharged mode by making it flinch several times. Once it's down, you can use the capture net to collect materials.

details.title: Rajang
details.info: Extremely territorial and aggressive. When enraged, it can destroy shock traps. Attack its tail to stop its rampage.

details.title: Furious Rajang
details.info: Unlike its counterpart, Furious Rajang has no tail, meaning it cannot be brought out of its enraged state.

details.title: Raging Brachydios
details.info: A Brachydios variant that is much larger than the normal species. The slime on its body will activate over time and detonate.

details.info: Known as a symbol of destruction, people fear even uttering it’s name. It’s rumoured to control all of the elements, but most, if not all, records of its existence have been burned.

details.title: Frostfang Barioth
details.info: A Barioth variant capable of spewing a sub-zero breath attack that it uses to slow down prey. Be careful, as this attack can freeze you as well.
